UR  - https://www.sciencedirect.com/science/article/pii/0378426689900381
AB  - In this paper, the short-run behavior of stock prices in the German stock market is investigated, and an implied bid-ask spread is calculated. The German stock market operates, for the most part, according to auction market principles, and bid and ask prices are not continuously posted by dealers. Yet implied spreads calculated from the serial covariance of transaction prices are positive and exhibit the same characteristics as implied spreads on U.S. dealer markets.
