AB  - The effects of unexpected variations in many macroeconomic variables on aggregate stock price indices are evaluated for Great Britain, West Germany and Switzerland. Quarterly data over the recent flexible exchange rate period are used. The results indicate that the effects of macroeconomic news are either very small or obscured by a low signal to noise ratio.
