SN  - 0378-4266
DO  - https://doi.org/10.1016/0378-4266(89)90040-X
UR  - https://www.sciencedirect.com/science/article/pii/037842668990040X
AB  - This paper analyses business groups, composed of legally independent firms connected through a network of cross-shareholdings. A model which allows to calculate the value of the firms of a group and the integrated ownership shares held by an outside stockholder, is described. A taxonomy for the collection of risk capital generalizing the one which applies for a single firm is proposed; the connection between the process of raising risk capital and the separation of ownership from control in business groups is demonstrated and given a formal mathematical description. Empirical evidence relating to the amount of risk capital collected by Italian business groups in the '80s and to the extent of the divorce between ownership and control is also provided.
ER  - 
